#First Task

def graph_instance(X,Y,Z,clas,velocity=False):
    
    ix = X[X["class"] == clas].iloc[-1]
    iy = Y[Y["class"] == clas].iloc[-1]
    iz = Z[Z["class"] == clas].iloc[-1]
    
    df = pd.DataFrame(columns=["X","Y","Z"])
    
    df["X"],df["Y"],df["Z"] = ix,iy,iz
    
    df = df[1:-1]
    
    if velocity == False:
        
        fig = plt.figure(figsize = (10, 7))
        ax = plt.axes(projection ="3d")

        ax.scatter3D(df["X"], df["Y"], df["Z"])
        plt.title("3D scatter plot of acceleration")

        plt.show()
    
    else:
        
        df["X_Vel"],df["Y_Vel"],df["Z_Vel"] = df["X"].cumsum(),df["Y"].cumsum(),df["Z"].cumsum()
        
        fig = plt.figure(figsize = (10, 7))
        ax = plt.axes(projection ="3d")

        ax.scatter3D(df["X_Vel"], df["Y_Vel"], df["Z_Vel"])
        plt.title("3D scatter plot of velocity")

        plt.show()

#Graphing 2 instances from each class, using the previous PCA results

def graph_time_series(df):    
    
    r1 = random.choice(list(df["time series id"]))
    r2 = random.choice(list(df["time series id"]))
    first = df[df["time series id"] == r1]
    second = df[df["time series id"] == r2]
    plt.title("This is the time series graph for {}".format(df["class"].iloc[0]))
    plt.plot(first["pca1"],color = "b")
    plt.plot(second["pca1"],color = "r")
    plt.show()

#Taks 3

pcas = []

for i in range(1,XYZ["class"].nunique()+1):
    
    m = XYZ[XYZ["class"] == i]
    
    pca = PCA()
    pca.fit(m[["X","Y","Z"]])
    print("\n","This is the PCA for the class {} :".format(i))
    print("All {} components: ".format(pca.n_components_),"\n\n",pca.components_,"\n")
    print("First component: ",pca.components_[0])
    print("Explained variance ratio: ",pca.explained_variance_ratio_)
    
    pcas.append(pca.components_[0])
